# Plan: Add PixelArt AI Provider to Vercel AI SDK

## Context

The Vercel AI SDK uses a layered provider architecture where each AI service is implemented as a separate package under `packages/<provider>`. This task adds a fictional `@ai-sdk/pixelart` provider that exclusively implements image generation — no language models, no embeddings. The provider must follow the established monorepo patterns exactly (package structure, TypeScript config, build config, exports, and the `ImageModelV3` interface).

The best reference provider to mirror is `@ai-sdk/fal` (`packages/fal/`), which is also image-focused and is comparably lean. The `ImageModelV3` interface (from `@ai-sdk/provider`) and utilities like `postJsonToApi`, `combineHeaders`, `createJsonResponseHandler`, `createJsonErrorResponseHandler`, and `withoutTrailingSlash` (from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`) must be used throughout.

---

## Files to Create

All files go in `packages/pixelart/`. No existing files are modified except `tsconfig.json` at the repo root (one reference added).

